              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is complete, then quasi-finiteness is equivalent to finiteness.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
              <fr:backmatter />
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>We could also give the usual polysyllogism (i), (ii), (iii), (iv), (v) for quasi-finite morphisms, but that doesn't seem necessary here.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
